Police have arrested and charged a man and woman over the discovery of a mass greyhound dog grave in Queensland .
A 71-year-old man and 64-year woman woman were charged with unlawfully possessing a firearm after a police search found a rifle and ammunition in a home in Bundaberg , Queensland , on Thursday .
The carcasses of more than 50 greyhounds were found at the bush site in Coonarr on Tuesday .